:::{#about-heading}

I am a researcher in English linguistics at Chemnitz University of Technology, working in the areas of second language perception and production, corpus linguistics and academic writing. 

Email: marina.ivanova[at]phil.tu-chemnitz.de

| Date     | News                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                       |
|----------|-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|
| 21.05.24 | Excited for two new articles on "German English-medium linguistics journal abstracts over the last 30 years" and "English MA Theses at a German University before and after the Bologna reform" published at *TOKEN: A Journal of English Linguistics. 16*  (see [Publications](https://mbisivan.github.io/pages/publications.html))                                                                                                                                  |
| 08.04.24 | I am happy to join the project [Declining Case: Inflectional Loss in Progress](https://www.smg.surrey.ac.uk/projects/declining-case-inflectional-loss-in-progress/) (University of Surrey) as a transcriber of Bulgarian interviews.                                                                                                                                    |
| 01.04.24 | I am happy to join the TU Chemnitz English and Digital Linguistics team as a researcher (Wissenschaftliche Mitarbeiterin).                                                                                                                                    |
| 02.02.24 | My PhD thesis on the perception and production of word stress cues in Slavic English varieties is now [online](https://nbn-resolving.org/urn:nbn:de:bsz:ch1-qucosa2-892831).                                                                                 |



